# Export user guide sync

The end-user doc is **`docs/Cortex Export - User Guide.md`**. When **any Cortex export** behavior, layout, or semantics change, update that guide in the **same change**—do not leave it stale.

## Export families covered

| Family | Code / CLI | User guide sections |
|--------|------------|---------------------|
| **Portfolio LLM context** | `cortex export-all`, `export-nightly` job · `src/export_llm_context_snapshot.py` | Portfolio LLM context · §1–§7 · status · ARR · portfolio prompts |
| **Per-customer Pendo** | `cortex --export-pendo`, `--export-pendo-detailed`, `--export-pendo-top-arr` · `src/export_customer_pendo_snapshot.py`, `src/export_pendo_detailed_snapshot.py`, `src/export_pendo_spreadsheet.py` | Per-customer Pendo export · §1–§12 · §13–§14 (detailed) · Pendo prompts |
| **Shared Drive layout** | `src/export_drive_layout.py`, `src/export_output_archive.py` · portfolio deck placement in `src/deck_orchestrator.py` | Where files live on Drive · For operators (paths) |

## When to update

Update the guide when a change affects anything a reader or LLM consumer would notice:

**Portfolio LLM (`LLM-Context-Portfolio`)**

- Markdown **section numbers, titles, or boundaries** (§1–§7, §3b / §3b-renewal / §3b-future, §3c, §4b, etc.)
- **What is included or excluded** per section (Pendo, Jira, Salesforce segments, CS Report, Slack, risk insights)
- **Customer status** vocabulary (`commercial_status`, current book vs churn / renewal / future)
- **ARR fields** or how customers are **ranked / capped** (top-N, env vars, ultimate-parent grouping)
- **Coverage / omission** messaging at the top of the export

**Per-customer export (`Customer Export (Nd)`)**

- Pendo export **section numbers or titles** (§1–§12; §13–§14 for detailed)
- **Markdown vs spreadsheet** pairing, stem/filename pattern, or lookback window in names (`7d`, `30d`)
- **Customer resolution** behavior (Pendo prefix vs alias) when user-facing
- Differences between **standard**, **detailed**, and **top-ARR batch** exports

**Drive layout (all exports)**

- **Persistent** vs **Historical Data/{date}/** dual-write paths
- Portfolio root (`Output/`) vs per-customer (`Output/Customer Exports/{Customer}/`)
- Monthly archive rollup under `Historical Data/{YYYY-MM}/`
- Scheduled **job names** or default windows when operators rely on them

**Operators**

- **CLI flags**, default lookback, size caps, or filters (`--customers-sf-allowlist`, `--skip-risk-insights`, `--no-drive`, etc.)
- New **example prompts** when a section is added or its purpose shifts materially

## What to skip

- Internal refactors with no user-visible export change
- Test-only or fixture tweaks that do not change export content or Drive placement
- Technical catalog field paths — those belong in `DATA_DICTIONARY.md`, not the user guide
- Deck slide content / design — `docs/PRESENTATION/` unless the change only affects export-style Drive filenames or layout documented in the guide

## How to update

- Write for **non-technical readers** (CS, AMs, leadership): plain English, short tables, example AI prompts where helpful
- Keep operator/CLI details in **For operators** at the end; keep Drive paths in **Where files live on Drive**
- If the guide is renamed or moved, update links in `docs/DATA-GOVERNANCE/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` and any other docs that reference it in the same change

## Completion check

Before marking export work done, confirm the user guide still matches:

1. **Portfolio LLM** — section map, status/ARR rules, caps, portfolio example prompts
2. **Per-customer Pendo** — section map (incl. detailed extras), spreadsheet note, Pendo example prompts
3. **Drive layout** — persistent filenames, historical day folders, portfolio vs `Customer Exports` bases
4. At least one prompt example for any **new or materially changed** section
